# %% [markdown]
# # 🏥 Clinical MoE OCR Pipeline v3.0 — Kaggle T4×2 Edition
#
# **Production-grade Mixture-of-Experts OCR pipeline** for clinical document
# text extraction. Implements an 8-stage pipeline grounded in a 32-paper
# research corpus [P1]–[P32].
#
# ## Pipeline Architecture
# ```
# INPUT (PDF/Image)
#   → Stage 0: Bifurcated Pre-processing          [P1][P3][P4][P5]
#   → Stage 1: Layout Analysis & Segmentation      [P6][P7][P15]
#   → Stage 2: Region Feature Extraction            [P1][P2]
#   → Stage 3: Hybrid MoE Router (SmolVLM-500M)    [P26][P27]
#   → Stage 4: OCR Expert Pool Execution            [P8][P9][P17]
#   → Stage 5: OCR Fusion & Post-processing         [P23][P24]
#   → Stage 6: MedGemma Medical Validation
#   → Stage 7: OCR Validation & Handoff
# OUTPUT: OCRResult → NLP Pipeline
# ```
#
# ## Expert Pool (Dual T4 Assignment)
# | Expert | Model | Role | Device |
# |--------|-------|------|--------|
# | **A** | TrOCR-Large [P8] | Handwriting (primary) | cuda:0 |
# | **B** | PaddleOCR PP-OCRv5 [P9] | Printed text (default) | cuda:0 |
# | **C** | Donut [P17] | Structured templated forms | cuda:0 |
# | **D** | Chandra OCR 2 (4-bit) | Multilingual & degraded | cuda:1 |
# | *Router* | SmolVLM-500M (4-bit) | VLM visual router | cuda:1 |
#
# ## Hardware: Kaggle T4×2 (2× 16 GB = 32 GB total VRAM)
# All experts **co-resident** — zero load/evict overhead.

